WEBVTT

00:01.250 --> 00:03.453
Wasn't this singing so rich this morning?

00:05.115 --> 00:06.076
How powerful.

00:07.418 --> 00:14.528
Well, if you'll hold tight there with me in second Corinthians 11, we plan to pick up this morning in verse 16.

00:15.549 --> 00:22.539
And I intended to get farther, but we will Lord willing make our way through verse 21.

00:25.142 --> 00:28.146
Cancer is something that has affected all of our lives.

00:28.866 --> 00:53.116
And we know how deadly cancer can be, which is why we take it so serious, which is why we do the best that we can to avoid it in any way that we can so help through healthy diet and exercise, rest, eliminating anxiety, watching our bodies and the symptoms of it to catch it early when detected.

00:54.057 --> 00:58.322
We know that the right treatment is crucial and to do so immediately.

00:59.394 --> 01:09.145
And what we see in life and in 2 Corinthians and in many of the New Testament letters is that sin in and of itself is a cancer.

01:10.106 --> 01:22.820
It's a cancer and we see it in Galatians chapter 5 where the Judaizers make their way back into the church as these Christians have now come under the lordship of Christ.

01:22.940 --> 01:24.562
They are serving their king

01:25.026 --> 01:35.542
And now these Judaizers are trying to bring them back under Jewish circumcision and Jewish ceremonial law and dietary laws in order to be saved.

01:35.642 --> 01:42.993
And Paul says this in Galatians 5, 9, a little 11, 11s, the whole law.

01:43.894 --> 01:44.515
What happened?

01:44.535 --> 01:46.198
You were running so well.

01:47.099 --> 01:49.202
And now you're being hindered from grace.

01:49.890 --> 01:58.841
We see in 1 Corinthians chapter 5 verse 9, a completely different situation in Corinth when immorality is beginning to plague this church.

01:58.921 --> 02:04.648
And Paul to them as well said, a little leavens, what?

02:05.169 --> 02:06.891
The whole lump.

02:06.911 --> 02:08.173
It eats its way through.

02:08.193 --> 02:13.119
The title of my sermon today is a cancer in the church.

02:13.680 --> 02:15.302
A cancer in the church.

02:16.243 --> 02:18.706
We've watched these false teachers continue

02:19.042 --> 02:29.395
to try to devour with their deception this church that Paul had bled for, sweat over, cried over, prayed for, labored for.

02:29.435 --> 02:33.921
They have undermined Paul and his apostolic authority.

02:34.201 --> 02:41.651
They are gloating in themselves and they have won over some, if not a sizable portion of the church.

02:42.832 --> 02:47.218
If you look with me in chapter 11, verses 16 through 21,

02:47.554 --> 02:53.820
Just in six verses in this section, we have two words that are dominating this section.

02:54.861 --> 03:00.286
The word full is used five times and the word boast is used six times.

03:01.147 --> 03:03.229
Now, if you hear a word once, it's important.

03:03.269 --> 03:11.797
If you hear it that many times, the repetition magnifies the emphasis on these two words, full and boast.

03:12.978 --> 03:17.362
I want you to see this morning, two realities regarding our response

03:17.762 --> 03:22.848
both the frauds and to fools among professing believers.

03:24.069 --> 03:35.762
Number one, in verses 16 through 18, we will note defending yourself before fools, the wind and the howl of defending yourself before fools.

03:37.244 --> 03:46.674
Number two, in verses 19 through 22, though we'll stop at verse 21, I want you to see secondly, exposing fools as frauds.

03:47.298 --> 03:49.501
the who and the how.

03:50.603 --> 04:02.842
As we read through Proverbs 26, one through 12 earlier, did you not hear fool over and over and the punch that it brings when you consider such folly?

04:04.244 --> 04:08.811
Look with me number one, defending yourself before fools, when and why.

04:08.891 --> 04:11.094
This is the situation Paul has been put in.

04:11.435 --> 04:12.757
Look with me in verse 16.

04:13.678 --> 04:16.242
Paul says, I repeat,

04:16.930 --> 04:19.132
Let no one think me foolish."

04:19.513 --> 04:20.073
There it is.

04:21.114 --> 04:30.684
But even if you do accept me or receive me, the King James says, as a fool, so that I too may boast a little.

04:31.745 --> 04:39.633
We are entering into now what scholars call Paul's famous full speech, the full speech.

04:40.594 --> 04:44.338
The word fool is used six times in 1 Corinthians,

04:44.546 --> 04:54.539
More so in the context of describing how God counts and even uses what the world sees as foolish for his own purposes.

04:55.680 --> 04:58.103
We read earlier and we'll return to shortly.

04:58.384 --> 05:06.334
First Corinthians 4 where Paul uses such biting sarcasm in order to reveal their foolishness.

05:06.654 --> 05:09.458
And so he does now in this full speech once again.

05:10.306 --> 05:19.939
Look with me in verse 16, this word fool used six times in this chapter, mostly right here in the passage before us, twice more in the next chapter.

05:20.039 --> 05:22.482
Paul is dealing with fools.

05:23.644 --> 05:34.458
And he doesn't want the church to consider him foolish, but if they will, at least they'll put up with him as much and in the way that he's already putting, they're putting up with true fools.

05:35.600 --> 05:40.306
Paul uses this word fool to say that he does not want to enter

05:40.738 --> 05:44.548
this foolish controversy among these false teachers.

05:44.889 --> 05:47.997
In other words, he's saying, I do not want to play your game.

05:48.358 --> 05:50.263
I do not want to adopt your ways.

05:50.483 --> 05:54.273
I will not be put on an equal playing field with you.

05:54.293 --> 05:57.842
I will not engage you as equals.

05:59.234 --> 06:11.810
And because the church refuses to defend Paul and receive his apostolic ministry, Paul is put in a position of doing something that normally he wouldn't do and normally one shouldn't do.

06:11.871 --> 06:17.698
He enters the arena of engagement with fools.

06:18.760 --> 06:21.964
And I believe that we see much and learn much through it.

06:23.346 --> 06:26.770
As we've already seen in we'll see in chapter 12 verse 11,

06:26.978 --> 06:29.943
The church is refusing to commend and receive Paul.

06:30.023 --> 06:36.854
Therefore, he will speak and boast of his own credentials before God, his own authority, his own faithfulness.

06:38.095 --> 06:49.874
And he says in chapter 12 verse six, if you'll turn over with me, because he speaks the truth, he may appear to be a fool and he may engage with fools, but he is not truly a fool.

06:50.594 --> 07:01.706
And we'll notice as Paul has put in this very embarrassing situation of boasting of himself that he boasts vastly different than that of the fools.

07:02.647 --> 07:07.393
The fools who commend themselves and Paul does so much differently.

07:08.594 --> 07:19.666
It's ironic that surely the church will listen to Paul as he commends himself for good reason since they put up with fools and these false teachers

07:19.842 --> 07:24.147
who do so for bad reason with foolish, underhanded motives.

07:25.669 --> 07:30.814
Look with me in verse one in chapter 11 where this conversation really begins.

07:32.396 --> 07:40.586
Paul is now picking up from when he said, I hope you will put up with me in a little foolishness.

07:41.587 --> 07:44.530
Yes, please put up with me.

07:45.474 --> 07:48.799
So he picks up now in verse 16, defending himself.

07:49.139 --> 07:55.950
And it's not just about his character, it's not just about a personal vendetta that he has with others.

07:56.350 --> 08:00.997
His apostolic ministry is hinging in the balance.

08:01.017 --> 08:14.898
And if they do not receive his ministry, which comes with the authority of God, and instead they continue to entertain the ministry of wolves, then their sanctification, if not their salvation hangs,

08:15.042 --> 08:17.566
in the balance.

08:17.586 --> 08:19.649
Look with me in chapter 12 verse 5.

08:21.732 --> 08:28.982
He says, on behalf of this man, I will boast, but on my own behalf, I will not boast, except of my weaknesses.

08:29.263 --> 08:39.698
Though if I should wish to boast, I would not be a fool, or I would be speaking the truth, but I refrain from it so that no one may think more of me

08:40.290 --> 08:43.335
then he sees in me or hears from me.

08:43.635 --> 08:48.823
Paul said in chapter 10 that he will not boast beyond proper limits.

08:48.843 --> 08:51.487
Do you ever hear someone boasting anything?

08:51.507 --> 08:54.191
That's pretty big britches there, boy.

08:54.251 --> 08:59.919
That's some big shoes to feel and certainly you can't feel them.

09:01.181 --> 09:05.368
Paul says, God's given me an authority to build you up, not to tear you down.

09:05.728 --> 09:09.714
And I will use it humbly ever so I may, but I will assert it

09:10.562 --> 09:12.164
when your good depends on it.

09:13.285 --> 09:18.850
Not to exalt himself, but to point to the one whom he represents.

09:18.870 --> 09:24.536
Look with me in chapter 11, verse 16, he says, so accept me or receive me.

09:25.016 --> 09:33.284
It could mean hear me out, endure listening to me, put up with me just for a moment, just for a moment.

09:34.505 --> 09:36.547
Humor me if you will.

09:37.808 --> 09:39.410
Look with me in verse 17.

09:40.994 --> 10:02.303
He says, what I am saying with this boastful confidence that which is perceived as boasting, I say not as the Lord or after the Lord or literally it could read according to or in accordance with the Lord would, but as a fool.

10:02.363 --> 10:10.034
We've seen this, this sort of phrasing, not from the Lord, not as the Lord,

10:11.074 --> 10:12.636
Anything, what is Paul doing?

10:12.696 --> 10:14.398
He's going quite off script.

10:14.418 --> 10:16.060
Is he speaking against the Lord?

10:16.441 --> 10:21.787
Is he now admitting freely that this is not inspired scripture, but his own opinion?

10:22.729 --> 10:25.752
Are there verses in the Bible where Paul speaks for himself?

10:26.894 --> 10:30.358
And it doesn't come with the authority of God and the answers, of course not.

10:31.720 --> 10:35.024
Paul says in 1 Corinthians 7, 12, something very similar.

10:35.064 --> 10:39.730
And he says that in the matter in 1 Corinthians 7,

10:40.002 --> 10:42.084
The Lord gave no direct command.

10:42.144 --> 10:45.607
He didn't quote something on that particular matter.

10:46.608 --> 10:54.997
But nonetheless, Paul, under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit, does speak in accordance with the full counsel of God in the mind of Christ.

10:56.638 --> 11:06.928
In the situation before us, this boasting of himself, this entering into a debate with fools, Paul is doing so reluctantly.

11:07.188 --> 11:08.850
He is doing so humbly.

11:10.114 --> 11:14.198
And he says in chapter 12, verse 11, you forced me to it, I never wanted to.

11:14.218 --> 11:23.389
Ordinarily, brothers and sisters in Christ, we do not engage with those who prove to be truly fools.

11:25.651 --> 11:31.017
And it's very clear that Paul will not interact with them in a sinful manner.

11:32.178 --> 11:39.346
What he's saying is that this is not the paradigm for Godly ministry, but he does so

11:39.682 --> 11:42.748
because the circumstances of a fallen world call for it.

11:44.170 --> 11:54.149
One scholar said, it's as if they ate so long at the table of fools that they couldn't digest the normal diet of saints.

11:55.651 --> 12:01.522
I wanna talk to you in a way that normally people would interact with one another.

12:02.274 --> 12:09.846
But because I obviously can't do that and you are entertaining fools and becoming fools yourself, we'll do this the hard way.

12:10.788 --> 12:15.135
We'll do this in a way in accordance that normally we wouldn't do it.

12:16.737 --> 12:18.680
I love how Matthew Henry explained it.

12:18.720 --> 12:29.618
He said, though not contrary to the Lord, it wasn't the Lord's normal commendation for his followers to praise and vindicate themselves.

12:30.658 --> 12:32.880
but rather to obeys themselves.

12:33.901 --> 12:42.469
And yet the circumstances before us prudence would call for such an approach in such a circumstance.

12:43.951 --> 12:44.732
And so he does.

12:47.014 --> 12:59.506
Look with me in verse 18, he says, since many boasts are rejoiced are glory according to the flesh, according to the carnal ways of this world, according

13:00.098 --> 13:05.966
to our sinful hearts to show off our own glory and to showcase ourselves.

13:06.327 --> 13:13.016
He says, if many are going to do that, then I'll tell you what, you forced me to it, I'll boast.

13:14.458 --> 13:22.369
And if anyone had anything to boast about, the Apostle Paul could rightly boast without even sinning.

13:22.389 --> 13:28.658
2 Corinthians 10, 12 said, listen, we have put away our carnal ways

13:28.738 --> 13:32.223
Don't regard anyone according to the flesh.

13:33.225 --> 13:34.767
Don't look at people like that.

13:36.229 --> 13:45.723
Don't look at people with the same lens that this world uses to size people up and judge them for good or for bad.

13:45.763 --> 13:48.928
Don't use external appearances.

13:49.008 --> 13:51.952
Don't use worldly standards.

13:51.972 --> 13:53.234
We've put that away.

13:54.370 --> 14:03.222
And it's so clear that these false teachers, we saw in chapter five, verse 12, they were boasting, but they were boasting about outward appearances.

14:04.283 --> 14:06.847
They were boasting about the worldly credentials.

14:07.107 --> 14:13.696
They'll go on and Paul will reveal that they're boasting about their worldly pedigree, their worldly resumes.

14:14.917 --> 14:21.586
They're boasting in such a way that they want to put their best foot forward, yet they don't have a single good feet.

14:22.242 --> 14:22.763
to them.

14:22.823 --> 14:29.249
They want to show themselves and showcase themselves for something that they are not for their own glory.

14:29.269 --> 14:32.512
Friends, what a reminder.

14:33.673 --> 14:36.616
People love to brag on themselves, don't they?

14:37.817 --> 14:44.904
If you want to get someone talking but you don't know how to engage in the conversation, here's a good rule of thumb.

14:45.845 --> 14:51.250
Just ask them about themselves because naturally we love to talk about ourselves, don't we?

14:52.226 --> 15:00.528
Matter of fact, for some people, every conversation always finds a way to hook one back to themselves.

15:02.233 --> 15:08.690
And how much more carnal people love to brag about how much they have.

15:09.218 --> 15:14.164
Love to brag about who they know to name drop their connections.

15:14.604 --> 15:17.047
Love to brag about what they've done.

15:17.407 --> 15:19.990
Love to brag about how much they know.

15:20.390 --> 15:22.953
Love to brag about how they look.

15:22.973 --> 15:25.236
Love to brag about what they can do.

15:25.276 --> 15:33.665
Even if in a sort of humble brag, as if it were supposed to be put forth in a humble way.

15:33.685 --> 15:37.970
Oh, it's so hard.

15:38.530 --> 15:39.491
being this smart.

15:40.472 --> 15:46.039
And you know, you don't understand how difficult it is being this good looking, do you?

15:47.621 --> 15:52.007
You just don't understand how hard it is to be as awesome as me.

15:55.511 --> 16:01.439
And yeah, much boasting amounts to little less than that.

16:01.479 --> 16:04.302
Our flash loves to be petted.

16:05.143 --> 16:07.346
And we love to put it out there for other people.

16:08.898 --> 16:21.941
And Paul calls this business in this church of trying to impress and basically what they're trying to do is play a game of what I would call trying to out self-congratulate one another.

16:21.961 --> 16:27.410
They are trying to out self-congratulate one another

16:27.810 --> 16:31.636
And Paul does not want to enter into that with his rivals.

16:32.037 --> 16:37.926
He makes very clear throughout 2 Corinthians, this is how we boast, and this is how we should boast.

16:38.207 --> 16:45.098
Chapter 1 verse 12, with simplicity and a sincerity of conscience by the grace of God.

16:45.138 --> 16:49.906
He boasted the evidence of God's grace.

16:50.210 --> 16:50.931
and the church.

16:51.211 --> 16:55.216
He boasted the church and how God's working in her and his hope for her.

16:55.556 --> 17:00.922
He boasts of his divine calling and authority to build up the church, not tear it down.

17:01.983 --> 17:09.011
Paul boasts in chapter 11 and 12 of his weaknesses because that shows that it's really Christ and not Paul.

17:10.974 --> 17:16.840
Paul was not arrogant, but Paul makes very clear in this passage.

17:16.880 --> 17:18.482
He was, however, confident.

17:19.650 --> 17:26.797
And there is a very fine line between arrogance and confidence.

17:27.277 --> 17:34.925
And Paul makes very clear that he is confident, but his confidence is in the new covenant ministry of Jesus Christ.

17:36.086 --> 17:38.128
His confidence is not in himself.

17:38.388 --> 17:43.973
His confidence is in the work of God and his grace and all of his covenant promises.

17:44.274 --> 17:45.855
And that he is confident.

17:47.357 --> 17:48.818
He puts no confidence

17:49.346 --> 17:54.632
and the flesh, you wake up and all of the things that you said last Sunday, you were not going to do.

17:54.912 --> 18:03.822
And all of the things you said that you were going to do, and by Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, all of it's frayed.

18:06.805 --> 18:18.098
And so he doesn't want to boast, but since they do, he goes on to boast and he'll lay these out in chapter 11 and everything that crucifies sin, everything that promotes holiness,

18:18.210 --> 18:21.154
He'll lay out his litany of sufferings for the church.

18:21.775 --> 18:30.568
They boast to exalt themselves, our boast and how I humble myself to receive nothing from you, but to lay down my life for you.

18:30.628 --> 18:33.833
And he doesn't even want to do that.

18:34.334 --> 18:38.881
In chapter 12, they boast probably of their mystical experiences.

18:40.523 --> 18:43.588
In the coming weeks, we'll see where Paul literally went to heaven.

18:44.729 --> 18:46.312
And he didn't write a book about it.

18:47.053 --> 18:47.954
And he didn't get a,

18:48.226 --> 18:49.267
a deal for it.

18:50.048 --> 19:00.157
And he didn't even really want to talk about it, but because he was pressed in order to show that he was so much more than they, he briefly mentions it and then moves on.

19:02.239 --> 19:07.024
He'll boast of his weaknesses and trials that magnify Christ in his life.

19:07.204 --> 19:15.291
He'll boast in chapter 12, verse 12 of his mighty works, but only because they show the stamp of God on his apostolic calling.

19:15.471 --> 19:18.194
And in all of this, look with me in chapter 12.

19:19.874 --> 19:34.751
In chapter 12, verse seven, even when Paul was boasting, not wanting to being forced into it, but not doing it in a sinful way, he says to keep me from becoming conceited.

19:34.791 --> 19:39.716
Look at me, God has a way of humbling you, doesn't he?

19:42.079 --> 19:44.782
Oh, I think you're doing so well there, huh?

19:45.823 --> 19:48.466
Doing right, fine without me, aren't you?

19:50.914 --> 19:53.657
Let you stumble for a moment.

19:53.957 --> 20:09.154
Not because God is judging us, but because God wants to teach us as he gives us confidence that we cannot even walk without holding his hand as the old hymn says.

20:10.796 --> 20:19.986
And sometimes we begin to get misplaced confidence in our flesh instead of Christ.

20:21.410 --> 20:23.293
Boy, the church seems to be boasting.

20:23.333 --> 20:26.838
Not only the false teachers, as Brian read earlier, the church is boasting.

20:28.520 --> 20:32.606
Everybody is mighty, fine, proud of themselves.

20:34.288 --> 20:38.273
Boy, it seems like this is a church full of what we had many years ago.

20:38.293 --> 20:47.266
A lot of people who are determined to win the most spiritual person of the year award, and Paul says, this is so foolish.

20:47.666 --> 20:50.290
Turn back with me to 1 Corinthians 4, verse 7.

20:52.962 --> 21:01.972
He'll go on and he'll say, of all of this boasting, how can you boast so much in yourself?

21:02.252 --> 21:03.654
Oh, you're so wise.

21:05.055 --> 21:08.059
You were, you're so rich.

21:08.499 --> 21:13.324
You pride yourself in all of your little petty pedigrees.

21:13.364 --> 21:15.326
We'll come back to this passage often.

21:17.549 --> 21:22.194
But he says, why, what do you have that you did not receive?

21:23.650 --> 21:27.896
If then you received it, why do you boast as if you did not receive it?

21:27.976 --> 21:32.342
Ladies and gentlemen, everything that you have is a gift from God.

21:32.382 --> 21:36.527
Everything that you are is a gift from God.

21:36.587 --> 21:41.073
Everything that you can do is a gift from God.

21:41.134 --> 21:53.330
So why do we boast as those who have not received from his hand everything that we have and can so quickly be taken away just as easily as it was given?

21:53.474 --> 21:57.198
So praise and boast in His holy name.

21:57.238 --> 22:08.869
The only boast that we have is in what God made us, what God has done for us, what God is doing, what God will do and in knowing God.

22:09.170 --> 22:21.522
If there is any claim to fame for the Christian, the only claim that we have to fame is that we know Jesus Christ and that we want to humbly

22:21.666 --> 22:23.868
serve Him for His glory, not our own.

22:27.312 --> 22:36.161
And in pressing this point, I want you to see the second one, which is the point in this section, exposing fools as frauds.

22:38.083 --> 22:41.547
Exposing fools as frauds, the who and the how.

22:41.927 --> 22:48.434
As we walk through this, I want you to know five dangers very practically.

22:49.058 --> 22:53.683
that we need to consider first of all as we check within our own souls.

22:54.163 --> 23:01.110
And secondly, I believe these five dangers present a grid to use in the discernment of other people.

23:03.192 --> 23:12.642
Look with me in verse 19, danger number one, one who is wise in his own eyes, wise in his own eyes.

23:14.724 --> 23:16.786
For you gladly bear

23:17.730 --> 23:25.281
put up with tolerate with fools being wise yourselves.

23:27.204 --> 23:33.433
Ladies and gentlemen, this is some of the most biting sarcasm in all of the Bible.

23:35.956 --> 23:45.650
It would be rivaled by what we've seen in 1 Corinthians chapter four, and it is some of the most scathing sarcasm

23:45.858 --> 23:47.920
used by the Apostle Paul.

23:49.862 --> 23:55.609
Sarcasm certainly has a place in the Christian life.

23:55.629 --> 24:02.035
And Paul brings it out as heavy artillery in this particular situation.

24:03.417 --> 24:05.319
Do you know sarcastic people in your life?

24:06.620 --> 24:08.142
There's a good chance you're one of them.

24:09.223 --> 24:15.570
And you can relate to what he's doing here, but I wanna caution us

24:16.450 --> 24:38.538
as we consider the use of this, which is appropriate in some situations, as a general rule of thumb, this tactic is typically not to be used for new believers and less mature believers who are not ready to wield such a tool as this.

24:40.281 --> 24:44.466
This is a tool that Paul uses wisely, he uses humbly,

24:44.706 --> 24:49.293
He uses sparingly and he uses very, very purposefully.

24:50.775 --> 25:08.320
And in using this tool of sarcasm, he uses it in order to expose and counteract these walls in order to take the blinders off the sheep in order to edify them, not to tear them down and to promote their truth and maturity in Jesus Christ.

25:08.680 --> 25:10.002
Look at what Paul says.

25:13.186 --> 25:16.151
He calls them so wise.

25:17.293 --> 25:22.822
Calvin says, with great applause, they put up with these fools.

25:24.665 --> 25:40.210
It's clearly sarcasm because he indicates that they count and even pride themselves on being so wise when clearly the evidence shows just the contrary and the logic does not follow.

25:40.770 --> 25:47.099
This church has such a severe lapse of judgment, and they are acting just the opposite.

25:47.780 --> 25:52.927
And they need to remember that God is going to destroy the wisdom of the wise.

25:52.947 --> 25:54.989
1 Corinthians 1.

25:56.211 --> 26:01.618
And everything that appears to be so wise, God will expose it for the foolishness that it truly is.

26:04.703 --> 26:10.130
And so in what sense did the church put up with, verses 19 and 20, or tolerate

26:10.306 --> 26:12.809
this nonsense, they're listening to it.

26:13.029 --> 26:14.511
They're influenced by it.

26:14.772 --> 26:16.133
They are condoning it.

26:16.474 --> 26:21.420
They are walking in accordance with these frauds as they have their own way.

26:21.780 --> 26:38.962
And Paul is basically saying this, counting themselves wise, they show themselves to be fools because they are putting up with those who are truly fools who count themselves to be wise.

26:41.442 --> 26:45.027
1 Corinthians 3, 18 says, let no one deceive himself.

