52:18.850 --> 52:26.182
He was crucified and stapled to a tree on our behalf undergoing far worse offense than this.

52:27.343 --> 52:35.196
And on the third day his humiliation turned into exaltation and he rose again from the grave and he reigns in glory.

52:37.800 --> 52:44.370
And he gives us the endurance and strength that we need as we empty ourselves and as we are full of him to serve him.

52:47.266 --> 52:55.073
Psalm 85, let me hear what God, the Lord will speak, for He will speak peace to His people.

52:56.435 --> 53:05.003
Listen to His saints, but let them not turn back to folly.

53:06.845 --> 53:16.914
Surely His salvation is near to those who fear Him, that glory may dwell

53:17.538 --> 53:18.179
in our land.

53:20.061 --> 53:21.363
Let us turn from our folly.

53:23.025 --> 53:27.972
Let us not turn back to it, but turn to Jesus Christ and live.

53:29.094 --> 53:29.554
Let's pray.

53:33.139 --> 53:46.898
Father, we pray that you would strengthen your people, that you would fill us with yourself, and we pray that you would make your covenant promises clear,

53:47.778 --> 53:50.102
and reel to us in a fresh way this morning.

53:52.265 --> 54:01.299
The London Baptist Confession says, the supper of the Lord Jesus was instituted by him the same night he was betrayed.

54:02.742 --> 54:11.015
It is to be observed in his churches to the end of the age as a perpetual remembrance and display of the sacrifice of himself and his death.

54:12.317 --> 54:15.602
It is given for the confirmation of the faith of believers

54:16.002 --> 54:27.519
and all the benefits of Christ's death, their spiritual nourishment and growth in Him, and their further engagement in and to all the duties they owe to Him.

54:28.801 --> 54:34.790
The Supper is to be a bond and pledge of their communion with Christ and with each other.

54:34.830 --> 54:45.106
As we come to the Supper this morning, emptied of ourself being renewed and filled with the newness of God,

54:46.594 --> 54:59.256
I want to remind you that this story begins in the garden where Adam and Eve, particularly of a tree that brought death and disease and depravity on all of humanity.

55:01.299 --> 55:12.178
And Jesus Christ was crucified on a tree to take all of our sin and all of our shame and to leave us with nothing but His covenant promises.

55:13.506 --> 55:27.722
And as we partake, we long for, we look for the final tree at the end of Revelation in glory that will have leaves, that will blossom for the life and flourishing of the nations.

55:29.023 --> 55:39.355
So Jesus says to his children this morning, turn from folly and come to me in E from my own hand.

55:41.097 --> 55:42.418
I want to encourage you

55:42.882 --> 55:57.857
in just a moment right now to consider your heart before God, any sin that the Lord may reveal, repent of it, turn from it and trust His grace in that.

55:59.058 --> 56:04.323
As we come together, we renew our covenant together with one another.

56:04.403 --> 56:08.567
We are one body in Christ and there ought to be no divisions between us.

56:09.608 --> 56:11.730
We are fed with the tokens

56:12.130 --> 56:23.483
of God's own fatherly hand, and we are strengthened and nourished, and we are pledging allegiance in a fresh way this morning to Jesus Christ.

56:25.405 --> 56:28.408
Let's pray for God's help as we give Him thanks.

56:31.732 --> 56:37.218
One Puritan prayed, God of all good, we bless you for the means of grace.

56:38.499 --> 56:41.202
Teach us to see in them your loving purposes,

56:41.858 --> 56:43.941
and the joy and strength of our souls.

56:45.022 --> 56:58.140
You have prepared for us a feast, and we are unworthy to sit down as guests, but we wholly rest on the merits of Jesus and hide ourselves beneath this righteousness.

56:59.062 --> 57:11.058
When we hear His tender invitation and see His wondrous grace, we cannot hesitate, but must come to you in love by your spirit in life and our faith, rightly to discern

57:11.202 --> 57:13.105
and spiritually to apprehend the Savior.

57:14.207 --> 57:26.625
While we gaze upon the emblems of our Savior's death, may we ponder why He died and hear Him say, I gave my life to purchasers, presented myself in offering to expiate your sin.

57:26.685 --> 57:40.466
Shed my blood to blot out your guilt, open my side to make you clean, endure your curses to set you free, bore your condemnation to satisfy divine justice,

57:41.474 --> 57:46.940
Oh, may I rightly grasp the breath and length of this design.

57:47.761 --> 57:57.232
Draw near obey, extend the hand, take the bread, receive the cup, eat and drink, testify before all men that I do for myself gladly in faith.

57:58.293 --> 58:04.700
Reverence and love receive my Lord to be the life, strength, nourishment, joy and delight.

58:06.623 --> 58:09.586
And finally in the supper, we remember his eternal love.

58:10.274 --> 58:27.072
boundless grace, infinite compassion, agony, cross redemption, and receive assurance of pardon, adoption, life, and glory as the outward elements nourish our body.

58:27.613 --> 58:40.146
So may your indwelling spirit invigorate our souls until that day when we hunger and thirst no more and sit with Jesus at his heavenly feast.

58:41.378 --> 58:52.348
Father, we pray that you would work in our hearts, exalt yourself, and that you would forgive and assure and strengthen your people.

58:53.209 --> 58:55.852
We give you thanks for these elements.

58:56.893 --> 59:11.346
And we pray that as signs and seals, tokens of your covenant promises, that you would bless your people and be united to us as we are to you more and more in Jesus' name, we pray.

59:11.970 --> 59:12.596
Amen.

